Clashes have erupted at a protest by fairground workers in the French city of Le Mans, who are demanding the right to set up stall in the town centre. Police pushed back hundreds of demonstrators as rioters targeted the city hall, where staff were evacuated. There are reports of injuries. Rioters pushed a burning caravan at police who fired rubber pellet grenades into the crowd, French media say. At one point protesters occupied the city’s railway station  “Spontaneous Riots” Put Kano on Life-Support - The untold story of a people in despair How grandpa-labourer was killed after Kano riots February 9